Description:
Perfect location.
After being in the same family for 62 years this comfortable family home has held a lot of good memories.
Presenting development potential (STCA) or incredible rental opportunities are possibilities available to the lucky buyer of this light and bright three-bedroom home.
The young family and first-time buyer will see the joy in securing this 697m2 (approx.) allotment with a view of extending the home into the large backyard as the family grows (STCA) or convert into a development later by building a modern dwelling at the rear (STCA).
For those with the simple desire of moving straight in, do so with confidence thanks to the sparkling presentation and easy-care nature of the single-level layout.
All three bedrooms are of generous proportions and offer an abundance of comfort, while a large light-filled lounge on entry presents a relaxed setting to unwind with the kids complete with gas heating and air-conditioning.
That essence of comfort extends to the bright open-plan meals/kitchen, which delights with its storage space and electric oven and gas cooktop, while a central family bathroom, separate laundry & secure garage with workshop are further highlights.
Public transport is an easy walk away and with the convenience of Corio Shopping Centre across the road. North Shore train station just 10 minutes away, the Princes Highway practically at your door and local schools just moments away, why live or invest anywhere else?

Description:
Good things come in small packages.
Located in a peaceful street, this home offers the perfect blend of stylish and low-maintenance living!
With all of Corio's amenities within walking distance from your front door, the location is simply superb. A short stroll will find you at the Corio Village Shopping Centre, where you can treat yourself at one of the many cafes or eateries, enjoy a touch of retail therapy, or simply grab the groceries with ease. Public transport is conveniently close by, while the Princes Highway provides easy access to Melbourne for commuters or the Geelong CBD.
Stepping inside the home you are greeted by the open plan living/dining/kitchen zone with ample light throughout. The kitchen takes care of all your cooking needs with extra cupboard space and a gas upright stove. Two bedrooms complete the home while the central bathroom features a shower and single vanity.
The generous sheltered decking area flows onto the small, lush yard - providing a tranquil setting for lazy weekends and casual gatherings with loved ones.
When it comes to low-maintenance living, it doesn't get better than this! You'll need to act swiftly to secure this absolute gem.

Description:
One for the family who loves to entertain.
This is the absolute best Corio has to offer, situated on a corner block on approx. 695m2, this fabulous property is perfect for the bigger families who love to entertain!
Comprising open kitchen/dining area with adjoining large living space or rumpus room, second living area at the front of the home, 4 generous bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, 2 toilets, double car garage plus extra shedding at the rear of the property.
Featuring built in robes in the bedrooms, walk in robe in the main plus split system heating and cooling, corner spa in the ensuite, dishwasher and breakfast bench in the kitchen, plenty of storage throughout the home, ducted heating, separate split system air conditioning, solar panels, water tank, garden shed and roller shutters on the front windows.
Outside there's so much space for almost any activity or game, an amazing undercover alfresco area perfect for year round entertaining and kids parties to be held, rear side access, storage for a boat in the back shed and still enough room for a caravan to be stored via the side access.
Located closely to Rose Park, Corio Shopping Centre and medical suites, ALDI, minutes drive to Princes Hwy and Ring Road for those that commute to Melbourne, and on the doorstep to the best coastline Australia has to offer. Don't miss out on one of Geelong fastest growing areas.

Description:
Make the right move for your family
Set on a corner block of approx 567m2, this spacious brick family home is ideally set up for the growing family who loves to entertain.
Consisting of 4 bedrooms, the generous master bedroom has an ensuite and large walk in robe. The 3 remaining bedrooms all have built-in robes and are located around the main bathroom.
The property has room to move, with 2 separate living areas providing a range of entertaining options for any family. Cooking for family and friends is made easy with the kitchen centred between the formal lounge, dining and family living areas. Plenty of bench and cupboard space makes dinner preparation a family affair.
Outside there is a huge undercover low maintenance area idea for entertaining and space for the kids to make wonderful childhood memories in the fully enclosed yard.
The property is a tradesman's dream with double garage and brick carport complete with roller door access.
With easy access to the Melbourne Ring Road and Corio Village Shopping Centre, the property ticks all of your boxes.
Terms 10% Deposit. Settlement 60 Days or sooner by agreement.

Description:
Perfect for All Types of Buyers!
Sitting on a generous allotment of 539sqm, situated in a growth suburb of Corio this property is a must to inspect. This 3-bedroom home is waiting for the new owners to renovate, invest or just move in and enjoy.
Comprising of spacious open plan lounge area with solid hardwood floors, air-conditioner and ducted heating for all year-round comfort. An updated fully functional kitchen with dishwasher, free standing oven/cook top, pantry and ample storage space. Down the hall you will find 3 generous size bedrooms all with BIR's serviced by the family bathroom with vanity and shower/bath.
Outside you have a pergola area ideal for entertaining and a large front yard enclosed perfect for children/ pets. Other features include a large laundry with separate toilet, garden shed, double lock-up garage and ample parking in driveway.
Located across the road from Hendy Street Reserve and within a short scroll to schools, shops & public transport. Only moments from the Corio Central Shopping Centre and minutes to the Geelong Ring Road for Melbourne and Surf Coast commuters and just around the corner from the Princes Highway. With being in a convenient location and full of potential, this property is worth considering.
